Sentencas: Nanocrystalline La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) powder with a specific surface area of 22.9 m(2) g(-1) and an average particle size of 175 nm was prepared by a nitrate-glycine solution combustion method and subsequent ball-milling.
Titulo: Low temperature processing of interlayer-free L0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The LSCF precalcined at 800 degrees C (LSCF-800) shows very good low-temperature sintering activity, and can well adhere to electrolyte after sintering at 700 degrees C and above.
Titulo: Low temperature processing of interlayer-free L0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The single cell Ni-YSZfYSZ/LSCF-800 with the cathode sintered at 750 degrees C demonstrates the lowest polarization resistance and good electrical generation performance, but poor cathode microstructure stability.
Titulo: Low temperature processing of interlayer-free L0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The sintering activity of LSCF cathode can be tailored through the control of the precalcination temperature of the precursor powder.
Titulo: Low temperature processing of interlayer-free L0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Precalcining of LSCF powder at 900 degrees C (LSCF-900) increases the optimum sintering temperature of the cathode to 850 degrees C and improves the microstructure stability.
Titulo: Low temperature processing of interlayer-free L0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cell Ni-YSZ/YSZ/LSCF-900 with this cathode demonstrates excellent generation performances with the maximum power density greater than 1.0 W cm(-2) and the power density of above 0.80 W cm(-2) at 0.7 V under operation at 700 degrees C. Low temperature processing of the interlayer-free LSCF cathode with good microstructure is beneficial to simplifying the cell structure and improving fuel cell performance.
Titulo: Low temperature processing of interlayer-free L0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
